<DIV class=3Dcomment id=3Dcomment-3265214><A id=3Dc3265214></A>
<P>In regard to your article on the meeting in Oslo, a ping back:</P>
<P>Private deal to approve OOXML? More evidence surfaces</P>
<P>Circumstantial evidence is mounting of one or more private deals =
having been=20
struck to approve DIS-29500 Office Open XML ("OOXML") as an =
international=20
standard, a deal that may have played a role in several key national=20
standardization bodies changing their voting position to approve =
OOXML.</P>
<P>[more]</P>
<P><A=20
href=3D"http://www.universal-interop-council.org/node/29">http://www.univ=
ersal-interop-council.org/node/29</A></P>
<DIV class=3Dcomment-footer><STRONG><A=20
title=3Dhttp://www.universal-interop-council.org=20
