<DIV class=3Dcomment id=3Dcomment-3273895><A id=3Dc3273895></A>
<P>Buck: Thanks for the link! It made my day. Excellent!</P>
<P>The BRM did not reject harmonization for ODF and OOXML: the sentiment =
of the=20
meeting was clearly in favour of it as a program. And there were several =

resolutions that progressed it: the ones relating to MathML and the =
whole=20
transitional conformance class.</P>
<P>What a lot of delegates discovered during the BRM was that =
convergence and=20
harmonization has to be a two way street (that both ODF and OOXML need =
features=20
to fit together), that it requires study and facts (such as the DIN =
work), that=20
it requires time and effort and negotiation (not something that can be =
done in a=20
week at a BRM), and that it requires actual draft text and a program of =
work.=20
Getting from A to C requires going through B. So the BRM concentrated on =
the=20
issues at hand, and getting IS 29500 into a state where the=20
co-evolution/convergence/interop/harmonization effort would be a natural =
result,=20
rather than something difficult.</P>
<P>For example, the fix for the CEILING() function introduced a prefix =
system=20
which can progress naturally into a namespace/module system with =
semantic=20
(though not syntactic) compatability with the ODF OpenFormula module =
system. The=20
BRM was like John the Baptist, calling for the roads to be smoothed, =
preparing=20
for something bigger, later, if my analogy is not too bizarre!</P>
<P>Secret deals? I think the trouble is that people don't have any idea =
of the=20
collegial way that ISO groups work. When some NBs say that they are not =
happy=20
that the BRM was too short, or that review time was too short, or =
whatever, the=20
other NBs *especially* those NBs who disagreed that the time was =
showstoppingly=20
too short will still treat the complaint with respect, and this is =
reflected in=20
the strong desire for SC34 to have a fast, efficient, pro-active =
maintenance=20
procedure. It is not a "You lost, shut up" system: in a consensus =
system, you=20
often don't get the program you ask for, but participants take very =
seriously=20
trying to find ways of identifying the underlying need and trying to at =
least=20
*part-way* address it.</P>
<P>If MS does not take the SC34 maintenance program seriously, I have no =
doubt=20
that IS 29500 will be destandardized in a year or two. The requirement =
for a=20
strong, more open maintenance process was one of the messages that =
really came=20
through strongly during and after the BRM, and I think it is certainly=20
understood by Ecma that they only had a successful ballot because of =
this=20
expectations by NBs.</P>
<P>However, you shouldn't think this was strange or unusual. No "secret =
deal".=20
<BR></P>
